President Obama honored the recipients of the National Medal of Science and National Medal of Technology and Innovation, which are the highest honors given by the US government to scientists, engineers, and inventors. The President also announced additional steps to help bring more innovative ideas to the market and create jobs. The National Medal of Science recognized individuals who made outstanding contributions to science and engineering, while the National Medal of Technology and Innovation recognized those who made lasting contributions to America's competitiveness and quality of life. The article listed the recipients of these medals and highlighted their notable contributions. Additionally, the article mentioned that the federal Manufacturing Extension Partnership (MEP) will launch a new online resource to assist manufacturers, tech firms, and entrepreneurs in turning their ideas into products and businesses. This resource will provide information on organizations and initiatives that offer capital, entrepreneurial support, technical assistance, and access to new markets. The aim is to bring together scattered information and make it easily accessible to help promote economic growth and innovation.